{
  "texts": [
    "This feature enables DRL to effectively handle the complicated optimization problems.",
    "Recently, FL has emerged as a promising technique to solve distributed optimization problems [71].",
    "Moreover, FL allows multiple edge devices to participate in the global training by uploading their training models instead of the raw data, which significantly reduces the communication overhead and improves the data security [72,73].Given the above advantages, AI is expected to address the challenges in the field of ISAC.",
    "For example, Zhong et al. [74] proposed a DL-based algorithm for online dual-function waveform design, which outperformed the traditional algorithms in terms of both sensing performance and communication rate.",
    "In addition, Sankar et al. [75] trained a deep neural network (DNN) for precoding design, demonstrating a lower computational complexity than the traditional algorithms."
  ]
}